<subSubSection id="1D9A6575FF86F93EEDD2497BFEE0FF07" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="73" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" type="description">
<paragraph id="553F36FEFF86F93DEDD2497BFDA7F882" blockId="5.[136,1452,1855,2061]" box="[136,546,1855,1881]" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF86F93DEDD2497BFE8BF882" box="[136,270,1855,1881]" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">Description</emphasis>
:— 
<bibRefCitation id="31114B0FFF86F93DEC75497BFD98F882" author="Jong, S. C. &amp; Davis, E. E." box="[303,541,1855,1881]" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" pagination="1351 - 1356" refId="ref5627" refString="Jong, S. C. &amp; Davis, E. E. (1972) Phialocephala humicola, a new hyphomycete. Mycologia 64 (6): 1351 - 1356. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00275514.1972.12019390" type="journal article" year="1972">Jong &amp; Davis (1972)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="553F36FEFF86F93EEDE74927FEE0FF07" blockId="5.[136,1452,1855,2061]" lastBlockId="6.[136,1451,158,221]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="73" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">
Notes:— 
<taxonomicName id="92804D7DFF86F93DEC784927FDB1F8A6" box="[290,564,1891,1917]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Mollisiaceae" genus="Phialocephala" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="humicola">
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF86F93DEC784927FDB1F8A6" box="[290,564,1891,1917]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">Phialocephala humicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was initially reported as saprophytes on soil in 
<collectingRegion id="9744F81CFF86F93DE91B4927FB46F8A6" box="[1089,1219,1891,1917]" country="United States of America" name="New Jersey" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">New Jersey</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="2D97766EFF86F93DE9974927FA86F8A6" box="[1229,1283,1891,1917]" name="United States of America" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">USA</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="31114B0FFF86F93DE8484927FF41F87A" author="Jong, S. C. &amp; Davis, E. E." pageId="5" pageNumber="72" pagination="1351 - 1356" refId="ref5627" refString="Jong, S. C. &amp; Davis, E. E. (1972) Phialocephala humicola, a new hyphomycete. Mycologia 64 (6): 1351 - 1356. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00275514.1972.12019390" type="journal article" year="1972">Jong &amp; Davis 1972</bibRefCitation>
). Although we did not isolate the 
<typeStatus id="8A3B885CFF86F93DEF1F49C3FDF0F87A" box="[581,629,1927,1953]" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">type</typeStatus>
strains, we have examined the DNA sequence data from ex-type culture and another culture deposited under that species name in GenBank. Multi-locus phylogenetic analyses indicate that this species formed a well-supported monophyletic lineage in 
<taxonomicName id="92804D7DFF86F93DEE0B498BFC57F832" box="[849,978,1999,2025]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Chaetosphaeriaceae" genus="Chloridium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Chaetosphaeriales" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF86F93DEE0B498BFC57F832" box="[849,978,1999,2025]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">Chloridium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and can be differentiated from the other species in 
<taxonomicName id="92804D7DFF86F93DEC5B49B7FE07F7D6" box="[257,386,2035,2061]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Chaetosphaeriaceae" genus="Chloridium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Chaetosphaeriales" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF86F93DEC5B49B7FE07F7D6" box="[257,386,2035,2061]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">Chloridium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its morphological characteristics and DNA sequence data (
<figureCitation id="CDBB2A7BFF86F93DE91549B7FB08F7D6" box="[1103,1165,2035,2061]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1824,1846]" captionTargetBox="[199,1408,886,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-270@3.[151,1436,868,1796]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Phylogram of RAxML analysis based on a combined ITS and LSU sequence dataset within Chloridium. Adautomilanezia caesalpiniae was used as outgroup. Bootstrap support values for Maximum likelihood and Maximum parsimony greater than 50%, and Bayesian posterior probabilities equal to or greater than 0.8 are indicated at the nodes (ML/BI/MP). Type strains are highlighted by a “*”, and our strain is in bold." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605363" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605363/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">Fig 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="CDBB2A7BFF86F93DE9C749B7FB2BF7D6" box="[1181,1198,2035,2061]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1227,1249]" captionTargetBox="[183,1395,224,1184]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[151,1436,190,1203]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Splitgraphs showing the results of the pairwise homoplasy index (PHI) test of newly described taxa and closely related species using both LogDet transformation and splits decomposition. PHI test results (Φw) &lt;0.05 indicate significant recombination within the dataset. Type strains and new taxa are indicated with “*” and bold, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605365" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605365/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">2</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="31114B0FFF86F93DE9E649B7FA1AF7D6" author="Jong, S. C. &amp; Davis, E. E." box="[1212,1439,2035,2061]" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" pagination="1351 - 1356" refId="ref5627" refString="Jong, S. C. &amp; Davis, E. E. (1972) Phialocephala humicola, a new hyphomycete. Mycologia 64 (6): 1351 - 1356. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00275514.1972.12019390" type="journal article" year="1972">Jong &amp; Davis 1972</bibRefCitation>
). Based on morphological characters and phylogenetic analyses, we therefore transferred 
<taxonomicName id="92804D7DFF85F93EE9394EDBFB62FF63" box="[1123,1255,158,184]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Mollisiaceae" genus="Phialocephala" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="73" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="humicola">
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF85F93EE9394EDBFB62FF63" box="[1123,1255,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="73">P. humicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="92804D7DFF85F93EE8564EDAFA08FF63" box="[1292,1421,158,184]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Chaetosphaeriaceae" genus="Chloridium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Chaetosphaeriales" pageId="6" pageNumber="73" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF85F93EE8564EDAFA08FF63" box="[1292,1421,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="73">Chloridium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a new combination.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
